  "observations": [
    "Sidebar shows folder tree of Docs with workspace switcher at top",
    "Each Doc has its own page tree (no separate database/page dichotomy — tables are blocks inside pages)",
    "Multiple tables can coexist on the same page as first-class blocks alongside text/buttons/AI",
    "Formula bar with live preview as user types (=Table.Column syntax with autocomplete)",
    "Buttons rendered as inline call-to-action with optional visibility-formula gating",
    "Column-type picker is a popover with grouped kinds (basic / lookup / formula / button / AI)",
    "Views appear as tabs above the table — switching kind (Table/Card/Kanban/Calendar/Timeline/Detail) is a one-click toggle",
    "Controlled view shows lock icon on filter chips — viewer cannot edit them",
    "Cross-doc block displays last-synced badge and refresh button in header",
    "Pack installation flow is a multi-step wizard (auth → permission scopes → confirm)",
    "Locked section indicated by lock icon on row gutter; even editors blocked from edit",
    "Page-level visibility toggle in page-meta sidebar — hidden pages greyed out for non-editors",
    "Publish flow: modal with checkbox tree of which pages to include in public version",
    "Template gallery is a full-page modal with category facets (CRM, OKR, Sprint, Roadmap, KB)",
    "AI inline prompt activated via slash-menu or `/ai` shortcut, result streams in-place",
    "Comments as right-rail thread, anchored to block or cell with target highlight",
    "Destructive actions (delete column, delete doc, uninstall pack) require typed confirmation",
    "Automations editor is a three-pane builder: Trigger → Condition → Action with formula slots",
    "Doc share modal has tabs: People (per-user role) / Link (commenter/viewer link) / Publish (public)",
    "Formula errors highlighted inline with red underline + hover tooltip showing parser message"
  ]
}